main_body:
Scope
This Regulation shall apply to cod, haddock, saithe and whiting caught in the North Sea and Skagerrak by any fishing gear other than:
(a) pelagic trawls, purse seines, driftnets and jiggers targeting herring, mackerel, and horse mackerel;
(b) pots;
(c) scallop dredges;
(d) gillnets.

Definitions
For the purpose of this Regulation, the following definitions shall apply:
(a) ICES (International Council for the Exploration of the Sea) zones means zones as defined in Council Regulation (EEC) No 3880/91 (3);
(b) ‘Skagerrak’ means the area bounded on the west by a line drawn from the Hanstholm lighthouse to the Lindesnes lighthouse and on the south by a line drawn from the Skagen lighthouse to the Tistlarna lighthouse and from this point to the nearest point on the Swedish coast;
(c) ‘North Sea’ means ICES zone IV;
(d) ‘haul’ means the act between the deployment and retrieval of a net.
